.TH "ubuntu\-lint" "1" "2026\-06\-22" ""
.SH NAME
ubuntu\-lint \(em packaging linter for Ubuntu uploads
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[CR]ubuntu\-lint [\-\-help] [\-\-verbose] [\-\-json] [\-\-source\-dir DIR] [\-\-changelog FILE] [\-\-changes\-file FILE] [\-\-all=(auto|off|warn|fail)] [\-\-<linter>=(auto|off|warn|fail)]...\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
ubuntu\-lint is a packaging linter focused on Ubuntu\-specific policies
and conventions.
It inspects Debian source package directories, changelogs, and .changes
files and runs modular lint checks.
.PP
If run with no explicit context flags and a \f[CR]debian/\f[R] directory
is present, ubuntu\-lint will infer context from the changelog and the
most recent .changes file.
Context may be provided explicitly using the context options below.
.PP
Most lint checks have an associated \f[CR]dput\-ng\f[R] hook defined for
easy linting at upload time.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-help, \-h\f[R]
Show help and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-verbose\f[R]
Enable verbose output.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-json\f[R]
Print results as JSON.
.SH CONTEXT OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-source\-dir DIR\f[R]
Path to Debian source package directory to use as context.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-changelog FILE\f[R]
Path to \f[CR]debian/changelog\f[R] to use as context.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-changes\-file FILE\f[R]
Path to a source .changes file to use as context.
.SH LINTER OPTIONS
Each lint has a corresponding flag \f[CR]\-\-<linter\-name>=\f[R] which
accepts one of: \f[CR]auto\f[R], \f[CR]off\f[R], \f[CR]warn\f[R],
\f[CR]fail\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
auto \(em use the lint\(cqs default behavior depending on whether the
target is a development or stable release.
.IP \(bu 2
warn \(em treat detected issues as warnings.
.IP \(bu 2
fail \(em treat detected issues as failures.
.IP \(bu 2
off \(em disable the check.
.PP
\f[CR]\-\-all=\f[R] sets the default level for all linters.
Any linter\-specific flags that come after take precedence.
.SH AVAILABLE LINTERS
.SS distribution\-invalid
Detects invalid or unsupported distribution field, such as incorrect
distribution names.
.SS missing\-bug\-references
Detects when the upload is missing Launchpad bug references in the
changelog.
.SS missing\-launchpad\-bugs\-fixed
Detects when the upload is missing Launchpad bug references (i.e.\ the
\f[CR]Launchpad\-Bugs\-Fixed\f[R] field) in the .changes file.
.SS missing\-git\-ubuntu\-references
Detects when changes file is missing \f[CR]git\-ubuntu\f[R] metadata
(i.e.\ the \f[CR]Vcs\-Git\f[R], \f[CR]Vcs\-Git\-Commit\f[R],
\f[CR]Vcs\-Git\-Ref\f[R] fields).
.SS git\-ubuntu\-references\-mismatch
Checks that if present, the \f[CR]git\-ubuntu\f[R] metadata in the
changes file is consistent with the remote.
.SS missing\-pending\-changelog\-entry
Detects when an upload\(cqs changelog is missing the entry of a pending
change, for example an upload that is still in \f[CR]\-proposed\f[R].
.SS missing\-ubuntu\-maintainer
Detects when the changes file has not set the \f[CR]Maintainer\f[R]
field to
\f[CR]Ubuntu Developers <ubuntu\-devel\-discuss\(atlists.ubuntu.com>\f[R].
.SS sru\-bug\-missing\-template
For SRU uploads, checks if the associated bugs have filled out the SRU
template.
.SS sru\-bug\-missing\-release\-tasks
For SRU uploads, checks if the associated bugs have the correct release
tasks set.
.SS sru\-version\-string\-breaks\-upgrades
For SRU uploads, checks if the version string could break upgrade paths.
.SS sru\-version\-string\-convention
For SRU uploads, checks if the version string follows Ubuntu and SRU
conventions.
.SS release\-mismatch
Attempts to detect inconsistencies in the version string and series
name, e.g.\ \f[CR]1.2.3\-0ubuntu1\(ti22.04.1\f[R] and \f[CR]noble\f[R]
(because the \f[CR]\(ti22.04.1\f[R] looks like it is meant for Ubuntu
22.04 LTS \(lqJammy Jellyfish\(rq, and \f[CR]noble\f[R] refers to Ubuntu
24.04 LTS \(lqNoble Numbat\(rq).
.PP
See \f[CR]ubuntu\-lint \-\-help\f[R] for the complete list.
.SH DPUT\-NG HOOKS
Most lint checks have an associated \f[CR]dput\-ng\f[R] hook which is
shipped in \f[CR]/etc/dput.d/hooks/<linter>.json\f[R].
If installed alongside \f[CR]dpug\-ng\f[R], these hooks will be invoked
with \f[CR]dput\-ng\f[R]\(cqs context at upload time.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run in current directory (auto\-detect context):
.PP
$ ubuntu\-lint
.PP
Run against an explicit source directory:
.PP
$ ubuntu\-lint \(ensource\-dir=/path/to/src
.PP
Disable a specific linter:
.PP
$ ubuntu\-lint \(enmissing\-git\-ubuntu\-references=off
.PP
Force all checks to be warnings:
.PP
$ ubuntu\-lint \(enall=warn
